A GeneralizedQuantifierRelation. (aFew_RelationToType PRED SOC1 SOC2) means that a few (aFew) elements of SOC1 bear PRED to an element of SOC2 -- i.e., a few elements X of SOC1 are such that, for some element Y of SOC2, (PRED X Y). It is equivalent to the more complex form: 
(aFew SOC1
  (TheSetOf ?X
    (thereExists ?Y
      (and
        (elementOf ?Y SOC2)
        (PRED ?X ?Y))))).
For example, (aFew_RelationToType owns Plumber Mansion) means that a few plumbers own mansions.

label: work-energy theorem
WorkEnergyTheorem
comment:
An instance of LawOfNature (q.v.). The work-energy theorem (or principle) states that the net work done on an object (in an event) is equal to the change in kinetic energy of that object (in that event).

One formulation of the WorkEnergyTheorem in CycL is: 

(mathEquals
  ((QPQuantityFn NetWorkQuantity) ?OBJ ?TEMP-THING)
  (DifferenceFn
    (MeasurementAtFn
      ((QPQuantityFn KineticEnergyQuantity) ?OBJ)
      (EndFn ?TEMP-THING))
    (MeasurementAtFn
      ((QPQuantityFn KineticEnergyQuantity) ?OBJ)
      (StartFn ?TEMP-THING))))
.
